title.narrative: HPN - HealthIT: Sustaining Use of District Health Information System II

description.narrative: (Kenya): Strategic Result Area 1: Health Information systems :HealthIT project provides technical support Ministry of Health (MOH) on evolution and strengthening of sustainable healthIT responsiveness to user needs. Provides vital data for planning, decision making, and accountability within the health sector. Journey to self-reliance (J2SR): project will build capacity and commitment for resilient and reliable information systems. It will support MOH at national and county level to generate quality data on reproductive, maternal, newborn, child and adolescent health (RMNCAH). It will also generate quality data on nutrition, HIV/TB and malaria program, for use in evidence-based decision making by all stakeholders in the health sector. Project will support MOH in tracking health commodities through end-to-end commodity management modules within the National HealthIT. It will support development of an Epidemic Preparedness and Response dashboard that pulls data from the electronic Integrated Disease Surveillance and Response system for epidemic threshold setting. It is implemented through MOH structures and local institutions, hence, it catalyzes change and builds individual and institutional capability of national and county institutions to own and sustain data management systems. Strategic Result Area 2: Electronic Health Records :Activities will focus on development, implementation and quality assurance of end-to-end electronic health records systems at priority health facilities. Records are useful for the management of RMNCAH, malaria, HIV/TB, diseases, as well as data on mortality, nutrition, and program., These are essential for monitoring programmatic performance and prioritization of interventions.Strategic Result Area 3: Partner monitoring and reporting systems:Activity supports the Kenya Health Information monthly reporting system, used by all partners in the management and reporting of health data.
